            "body": "<p>You need to create an instance of the array (in Java, an array is an object -even if the array is of primitive types-)<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private char[] w = new char[numberBigEnough];\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Note that I would rather use a more dynamic approach, v.g. using a <code>StringBuilder<\/code> instance. That way you do not have to guess the line's length to specify the array dimensions.<\/p>\n",
